description.narrative:
UNICEF Malaysia initiate response on COVID19 immediately through its allies and partners reaching 1,634,798 people on COVID-19 related messages on prevention and access to services and engaged 181,854 youths on online initiatives on COVID-19 related mental health and psychosocial support. In addition, UNICEF provided the essential hygiene items and health education sessions to 10,880 children and their families from the vulnerable communities across the country. To support online learning during the lock down, UNICEF supported the Ministry of Education in online teaching capacity through google classroom platform that results in 2,380 teachers from 1,570 schools accessed to the learning opportunity.
